  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dda\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0d87\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dcf \u0db1\u0db8\u0dca \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0da2\u0dcf\u0dad\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0daf\u0dba\u0dad\u0dca \u0d89\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "If the parliament is touched, democracy is over",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "President Ranil Wickramasinghe questioned whether those who came to occupy the Parliament were repressed and were not treated properly, so what should have been done was to serve them cups of tea from the Parliament canteen.",
        "President Ranil Wickramasinghe said this while addressing the ceremony held at Bambalapitiya Police Field Force Headquarters today (03) on the occasion of Sri Lanka's 156th Police Day.",
        "If anyone tries to remove the Prime Minister or the Cabinet without the Parliament, they are violating the Constitution. It cannot be called a heroic act. We had to face such a situation.",
        "Last March, young people joined together and started a movement called struggle against a government. They acted peacefully. They showed their skills in various fields. No one can question that. They carried out the protest peacefully without violence. Unfortunately, last June, the peaceful group was removed and the movement was seized by the violent. They seized the government buildings. They also tried to seize the parliament.",
        "This is a violation of the rule of law as well as the constitution and also a loss of universal suffrage of the people. At that time the parliament was protected because the army and the police worked to protect it."
      ],
